````console
$ python -m snipinator.cli --help
Usage: python -m snipinator.cli [-h] -t TEMPLATE [--cwd CWD] [-a ARGS]
                                [--templates-searchpath TEMPLATES_SEARCHPATH]
                                [-o OUTPUT] [--rm] [--check]
                                [--warning-message WARNING_MESSAGE]
                                [--chmod CHMOD]

CLI: Python code snipinator for markdown files, e.g READMEs, from actual
(testable) code.

Optional Arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -t, --template TEMPLATE
                        Path to the template file. Use "-" for stdin.
  --cwd CWD             Directory to use as the base for snippet paths in the
                        template. Defaults to the current working directory.
  -a, --args ARGS       JSON string with template arguments. Any extra values
                        the user wishes to pass to the template, e.g.
                        `{'name': 'John'}` if they wish to render variables as
                        Jinja2 is capable of. Defaults to {}.
  --templates-searchpath TEMPLATES_SEARCHPATH
                        Path to the directory with templates for include
                        directives etc. Defaults to None, which means nothing
                        can be included using Jinja2's include directives,
                        which most users won't be needing.
  -o, --output OUTPUT   Path to the output file. Use "-" for stdout. Defaults
                        to "-".
  --rm                  Remove any existing file at the output path, before
                        writing the new one; useful if the existing file might
                        be write protected.
  --check               Check if the output file is the same as the rendered
                        text, and exit with a non-zero status code if it is
                        not. Does not write the file. Ignores options that
                        modify the file (e.g --rm and --chmod). Useful for CI
                        pipelines. Defaults to False.
  --warning-message WARNING_MESSAGE
                        Warning message to include in the output file. To
                        prevent accidentally editing generated file. Defaults
                        to the default warning message.
  --chmod CHMOD         Change the mode (permissions) of the output file, an
                        octant (see chmod help for more info) e.g 444 or 555.
                        To prevent accidentally editing generated file.
                        Defaults to None.

````

<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="410.4" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-16)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="434.8" textLength="549" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-17)">the user wishes to pass to the template, e.g.</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="434.8" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-17)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="459.2" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-18)">`</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r6" x="305" y="459.2" textLength="195.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-18)">{'name': 'John'}</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="500.2" y="459.2" textLength="451.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-18)">` if they wish to render variables as</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="459.2" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-18)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="483.6" textLength="451.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-19)">Jinja2 is capable of. Defaults to {}.</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="483.6" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-19)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="24.4" y="508" textLength="268.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-20)">--templates-searchpath</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r5" x="305" y="508" textLength="244" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-20)">TEMPLATES_SEARCHPATH</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="508" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-20)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="532.4" textLength="585.6" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-21)">Path to the directory with templates for include</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="532.4" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-21)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="556.8" textLength="646.6" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-22)">directives etc. Defaults to None, which means nothing</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="556.8" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-22)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="581.2" textLength="610" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-23)">can be included using Jinja2's include directives,</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="581.2" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-23)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="605.6" textLength="414.8" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-24)">which most users won't be needing.</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="605.6" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-24)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="24.4" y="630" textLength="24.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-25)">-o</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="48.8" y="630" textLength="24.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-25)">, </text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="73.2" y="630" textLength="97.6" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-25)">--output</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r5" x="183" y="630" textLength="73.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-25)">OUTPUT</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="630" textLength="646.6" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-25)">Path to the output file. Use &quot;-&quot; for stdout. Defaults</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="630" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-25)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="654.4" textLength="85.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-26)">to &quot;-&quot;.</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="654.4" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-26)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="24.4" y="678.8" textLength="48.8" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-27)">--rm</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="678.8" textLength="622.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-27)">Remove any existing file at the output path, before</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="678.8" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-27)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="703.2" textLength="658.8" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-28)">writing the new one; useful if the existing file might</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="703.2" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-28)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="727.6" textLength="231.8" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-29)">be write protected.</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="727.6" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-29)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="24.4" y="752" textLength="85.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-30)">--check</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="752" textLength="634.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-30)">Check if the output file is the same as the rendered</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="752" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-30)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="776.4" textLength="622.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-31)">text, and exit with a non-zero status code if it is</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="776.4" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-31)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="800.8" textLength="610" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-32)">not. Does not write the file. Ignores options that</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="800.8" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-32)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="825.2" textLength="256.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-33)">modify the file (e.g </text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="549" y="825.2" textLength="48.8" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-33)">--rm</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="597.8" y="825.2" textLength="61" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-33)"> and </text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r4" x="658.8" y="825.2" textLength="85.4" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-33)">--chmod</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="744.2" y="825.2" textLength="195.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-33)">). Useful for CI</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="976" y="825.2" textLength="12.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-33)">
</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="849.6" textLength="353.8" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-34)">pipelines. Defaults to False.</text>

</text>

</text>

</text>
<text class="terminal-607392315-r1" x="292.8" y="947.2" textLength="378.2" clip-path="url(#terminal-607392315-line-38)">to the default warning message.</text>

</text>

</text>
